  <text>
    <body>
      <ab type="lido:objectWorkType">Leaflet</ab>
      <ab subtype="creation" type="lido:event">
        <date>1951 after</date>
      </ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The leaflet features a framed photograph of a man and woman, both looking just past the camera the camera and dressed western-style. He has a revolver in his right hand, pointing in the same direction. Their bodies are closely pressed together. He grasps her right shoulder with his left hand; her arms are clutched around his waist. A wooden wall is seen in the background, while behind the woman a hat rests on a pile of straw. The Serbo-Croatian film title ‘Pustinja straha’ (Desert of fear) is printed in the lower section – in the English original: ‘Along the Great Divide’.</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">In the corner top right the handwritten number 3 is attached, probably an outdated registration number. The film was directed by Raoul Walsh and was released in 1951. Kirk Douglas and Virginia Mayo play the leading roles.</ab>
